from pjc peter j card subject re over zealou shuttle critic we ve have the the great western the dunno and the great northern postulate a brunel s masterpiece keep box the compas chap you ll get round to it eventually the great western wa a highly successful transatlantic mail ship with hybrid sail and steam propulsion the great eastern which break the giant financially and otherwise wa a revolutionary leap forward in ship design a thirty thousand ton all steel vessel with primary steam propulsion it wa at the time easily the biggest ocean go vessel ever build brunel take advantage of the fact that cargo and or fuel capacity rise with the cube of scale while drag rise with the square so a really big ship could steam thousand of mile without coal unfortunately there wa no real market for such a beast at the time and it wa eventually sell off at scrap value a another poster say it then go on to a successful career a a telegraph cable lay ship it wa in fact the only ship of it day capable of lay a transatlantic cable in one go with the endurance and capacity to carry the huge reel all the way and the manoeuverabilty to dredge for defective section see arthur c clarke s book how the world wa one i think that s right if that s how the shuttle go down in history a a technical triumph and a financial disaster for the builder it would not be entirely ignoble but i doubt if history will be so charitable it true the shuttle can do thing no other launch system can do but be they worth do with low cost acces to space you could have an affordable space station for do shuttle-like extend man mission a it be the shuttle be not so much a space-truck a a space-rv only not so cheap to run peter card joint european toru abingdon oxfordshire uk tel fax email pjc or compuserve it wasnt me it wa the other they make me do it disclaimer please note that the above be a personal view and should not be construe a an official comment from the jet project 